10:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Who Should Choose Which?"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"The ideal user for each platform differs considerably. Relume is best suited for web designers, agencies, Webflow users, making it a strong choice if you fall into any of these categories. Tome, meanwhile, shines for sales teams, founders, creative professionals, which means it may be the better pick if your needs align with those use cases.\n\nFounded in 2022, Relume describes itself as \"AI website builder that generates sitemaps and wireframes from text prompts.\" Tome, established in 2020, positions itself as \"AI-powered storytelling and presentation platform for modern teams.\" Both platforms have been in the market for a similar duration, giving each ample time to refine their offerings and build a loyal user base."}]]}]
11:["$","div",null,{"className":"verdict-box","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Our Verdict"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"After analyzing all the data, **Tome** comes out slightly ahead in this comparison, thanks to more features (9 vs 6), availability of a free plan. However, this does not mean Relume is a poor choice — far from it. Relume excels in its own right, particularly for web designers and agencies.\n\nOur recommendation: if you value ai generates entire narratives, go with Tome. If ai sitemap and wireframe generation matters more to you, Relume is the way to go. Either way, both are solid platforms that have earned their place in the market."}]]}]
